    <questiontext format="moodle_auto_format">
				<text><![CDATA[<p class="HELM_exercise">Exercise</p>

 <p>A man owns a house in town and a cottage in the country. In any one year the probability of the town house being burgled is \(\displaystyle{{@cc@}}\) and the probability of the country cottage being burgled is\(\displaystyle{{@dd@}}\).</p>
<p>In any one year what is the probability that:</p>

<ol class="HELM_parts">
  <li><p>Both will be burgled? [[input:ans2]] [[validation:ans2]] [[feedback:prt2]]</p></li>
  <li><p>One or the other (but not both) will be burgled? [[input:ans3]] [[validation:ans3]] [[feedback:prt3]]</p></li>
</ol>]]></text>
		</questiontext>
    <generalfeedback format="moodle_auto_format">
				<text><![CDATA[<p>A man owns a house in town and a cottage in the country. In any one year the probability of the town house being burgled is \(\displaystyle{{@cc@}}\) and the probability of the country cottage being burgled is\(\displaystyle{{@dd@}}\).</p>

<ol class="HELM_parts">
    <li>
        <p>\(H=\{\)house is burgled\(\}\ \ C=\{\)cottage is burgled\(\}\) \[\text{P}(H\cap C)=\text{P}(H)\text{P}(C)=\left({@cc@}\right)\left({@dd@}\right)={@ta21@}\] since events independent.</p>
    </li>
    <li>
        <p>\[\begin{align} \text{P(one or the other (but not both))} &amp; = \text{P}((H \cap C')\cup (H' \cap C)) \\ &amp; =\text{P}(H\cap C')+\text{P}(H'\cap C) \\ &amp;= \text{P}(H)\text{P}(C')+\text{P}(H')\text{P}(C) \\ &amp; = \left({@cc@}\right)\left({@ndd@}\right)+\left({@ncc@}\right)\left({@dd@}\right) \\ &amp;={@ta22@}. \end{align}\]</p>
    </li>
</ol>]]></text>
		</generalfeedback>
